# Lore-SM3 KEM Implementations README

This package contains the SM3-based Lore KEM algorithm implementations.

## Directory Structure

```
Implementations/
├── Reference_Implementation/
│   ├── Lore-L1/
│   ├── Lore-L2/
│   ├── Lore-L3/
│   └── Lore-L4/
├── Optimized_Implementation/
│   ├── Lore-L1/          (AVX2-optimized)
│   ├── Lore-L2/
│   ├── Lore-L3/
│   └── Lore-L4/
├── Additional_Implementation/
│   └── README
└── README
```

## Directory Description

`Reference_Implementation/` contains the portable ISO C reference implementation for each algorithm instance.

`Optimized_Implementation/` contains the AVX2-optimized implementation for each algorithm instance.

`Additional_Implementation/` is reserved for additional platform-specific implementations (e.g., ARM NEON).

Each `Lore-L*` directory is one algorithm instance and contains the source files, headers, `Makefile`, and KAT driver for that instance.

## Common File Description

- `api.h` — public API parameters and byte lengths.
- `params.h` — algorithm instance parameters.
- `kem.c/h` — KEM implementation.
- `pke.c/h` — underlying public-key encryption implementation.
- `indcpa.c/h` — underlying IND-CPA encryption implementation.
- `poly.c/h`, `polyvec.c/h`, `ntt.c/h`, `reduce.c/h` — polynomial arithmetic and transform routines.
- `sampler.c/h` — sampling routines.
- `verify.c/h` — verification and conditional move routines.
- `toomcook.c/h` — Toom-Cook multiplication.
- `bch_codec.c/h` — BCH error-correcting codec.
- `symmetric.c/h` — symmetric primitive abstraction layer.
- `randombytes.c/h` — system random number generator.
- `sm3.c/h`, `sm3_xof.c/h` — SM3 hash and XOF.
- `KEM_AlgorithmInstance.c/h` — API_PKC wrapper for key generation, encapsulation, and decapsulation.
- `KAT_KEM.c` — known-answer test driver.
- `drng.c/h` — deterministic random generator used by the KAT driver.
- `auxfunc.c/h` — auxiliary functions.
- `avx2_utils.h` — AVX2 helper macros (optimized implementation only).
- `Makefile` — build script for the instance.
- `simd/` — SIMD-optimized routines (optimized implementation only).

## Build and Run

### Reference Implementation

```bash
for L in 1 2 3 4; do
  cd Reference_Implementation/Lore-L${L}
  make clean
  make KAT_KEM_${L}
  ./KAT_KEM_${L}
  cd ../../
done
```

### Optimized Implementation (AVX2)

```bash
for L in 1 2 3 4; do
  cd Optimized_Implementation/Lore-L${L}
  make clean
  make KAT_KEM_${L}
  ./KAT_KEM_${L}
  cd ../../
done
```

## Level Parameters

| Level | K    | N    | Security (bits) |
|-------|------|------|-----------------|
| L1    | 1    | 512  | 128             |
| L2    | 2    | 512  | 256             |
| L3    | 3    | 512  | 384             |
| L4    | 3    | 768  | 512             |

## Test Vectors

Test vectors generated by the KAT driver are provided in the `Test_Vectors/` directory.
